Rob Eger wrote:

&gt; I might have been misunderstanding what the Add to Frontier was supposed
&gt; to do, and in light of your comment it makes sense.  The frontier will
&gt; be determined based on the original seed list in the case of a domain
&gt; scope crawl, and adding a new URL to the frontier via Add to Frontier
&gt; would be evaluated within that context, but adding them to the seed list
&gt; would make them part of the frontier.
&gt;
&gt; Am I understanding correctly now?

Yes.  Adding to the seed list changes scope (And adds the URI to the 
queue).  Adding via the Frontier screen does not alter scope.  It just 
adds item to queue.
